&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;G5 Respiratory High Care Unit offers the opportunity to develop your clinical skills caring for acute respiratory patients. Responsible for patients with advanced and complex respiratory disease, failure and in some cases COVID-19 requiring non-invasive ventilation (NIV) High Flow Oxygen and proning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Unit is a fast paced and challenging. You will be working with a highly skilled, supportive and encouraging team with an experienced and established management team who is passionate and committed to delivering high quality safe nursing care and intervention. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be offered the opportunity to develop both clinically and professionally within a supportive environment and to work with an inter- professional team to deliver the integrated critical care strategy and other national and local initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Closing date 10/11/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
